        <num>CC 1588</num>
        <heading>1588.  Joint or separate legacy</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1588.  Joint or separate legacy
A legacy to more than one person is either joint or separate.  It is separate when the testator assigns shares and joint when he does not.  Nevertheless, the testator may make a legacy joint or separate by expressly designating it  as such.</p>
        </content>
